rComments: He doesn't know much about how to give the knowledge to students, so when looking at his assignment or exam questions, you may not be able to connect what you learn from the class. In addition, his hand writing is very bad so that his class notes are almost unable to read.

The expectations are clearly laid out for all students in the syllabus. His slide shows prepare you with everything you need and the DGD questions are great tools for studying. This class is all about the HOW to do it; ignore the WHY. Tikuisis is there to help you if you need it, but it all comes down to the final; worth 55% of your final grade.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things', 'Test heavy']

rComments: Professor Tikuisis was great with thoroughly explaining concepts. The classes were done with many examples that correlated with testing. Attend all classes and pay attention and a good grade should be achieved.

He is not the worst professor that I have ever met, he is just bad in general. I tried to go to his lectures and followed his pace of learning, but the outcome was bad. His teaching is like going into surgery in which a surgeon removes your brain instead of the blood clots. You are better off practising everything yourself, mate. Don't count on him

Practice, Practice, practice. The key to success in this course is to be extremely familiar with the materials learnt in the lectures. Prof Tikuisis simply becomes a plank of wood when he is teaching the course content, and his teaching has caused an immeasurable damage to my brain that is almost on par with the damage during Lisbon earthquake. RUN

Available outside of class and very helpful in this aspect. Fair grading and very possible to do well. Lectures are horrendous and very incoherent. Often get stuck on assignment questions due to how poorly the material is presented. Get ready to learn on you own and take a tylenol after each one of his lectures.

Prof Tikuisis proves that being a professor requires experience, talents and attitudes, which are something that prof Tikuisis does not have unfortunately. The lectures are completely gibberish and exams are so difficult that only Euclid himself can solve the problems. If I have to spend 24 hour finding resources and teaching myself, why take yours

The professor is extremely helpful outside of class and office hours. He assures that all students understand well each part and will go above and beyond to make sure that you understand very well the topic. The course wasnt that easy but by putting the effort and asking further explanation to the prof i was able to pass with a B.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class', 'Amazing lectures ']

rComments: I enjoyed MAT2122 taught by Professor Tikuisis. Multivariable calculus is a serious subject and requires lots of study. It is not the fault of Professor Tikuisis that he is unable to inject knowledge into the brains of students. Success in higher mathematics requires rigorous study, which seems like most students are not willing to do.

If you take his class, then I suggest that you drop it as soon as possible because you wont learn anything in his lectures and you have to do tons of exercise yourself to do well. He is willing to answer questions but his teaching skills are so awful that makes the movie cats look like a masterpiece. 10k just to get this level of education.

One of the worst professors at this university. He doesnt have any experience or skills in teaching and he is unwilling to change his teaching style despite criticism. Save your time and go study something else because he is not worth the tuition I paid for education. Avoid if you can.

Lectures were comprehensive but time-consuming as his notes were somewhat unclear. All the tools to succeed are in DGD's and examples in the lectures. Assignments were well written; not too time-consuming and tested your knowledge of the content. Likes to explain the more intuitive side of concepts; some students might find this useful.

A professor who cannot teach you anything! Professor Tikuisis demonstrates that knowing something is far different from teaching something. He clearly can solve these problems himself, but he just doesnt know how to pass the knowledge to others. One of the most frustrating classes I have taken so far in my lifetime.

Literraly THE worst prof to ever exist. Illegible handwriting, has no idea how to potray information, asks the most difficult questions, with long computations that take hours. JUST AVOID HIM. I should've listened to the upper year students. I just want my money back. This was ridiculous

Youve got to be a genius to make an extremely easy course ten times more complicated than it is supposed to be, and Prof Tikuisis did it with no sweat. Right at this point, it would be a waste of time to go to his lectures instead of doing exercise questions and figuring out things on your own. I should give YouTube my tuition instead of him.
Easy class and didn't do homework. Take notes of the examples in class and you'll be fine.

Hey Aaron I didn't take your class to study the textbook myself and read between the lines; but of course that's asking too much of Mr. Tikuisis. His notes are extremely jumbled and incoherent. The cherry on top is that he also has illegible handwriting!

Probably one of the worst professors I have encountered at uOttawa; and that's a tall order. This guy will sit there for hours reciting Math words without explaining them. He will throw definitions and propositions at you without bothering to show you examples. Just absolutely atrocious, do not take your chances.

This is how classes with Mr. Tikuisis will go. He will teach you concepts A, B, and C but really concepts A.5, B.5, C.5 will be on the test/exams. He misses out on everything in between and it is very frustrating. Good luck.
He simply says out loud what he has already written down in his ineligible handwriting. There is nothing to learn. If you like hearing a man recite math terms for hours on end go ahead.
Very frustrating experience with him.

Prof Aaron is one of the funniest people that I have ever met in my life. His monotone is very funny and it actually makes me want to listen to his classes. The course material is so easy that even a 5-year old toddler can get an A at least. Stop criticising Prof Aaron because every math guy acts like him. It is normal.

The prof did not help students to learn course materials at all! I spent a huge amount of time figuring out different Math questions on my own. I am very surprised to see that there are people who actually give him high ratings. Prof is a nice person but cannot teach well. A PhD prof who can't even teach first-year class well and yet he gets paid.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Test heavy', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Professor Tikuisis was very accommodating during this semesters situation. He allowed me to move my midterm. Hes very kind and accessible outside his office hours. I strongly disliked the powerpoints he put up it would have been much better if he taught by the chalkboard because I felt I didnt learn as well. Go to the DGDs and get the textbook

Prof Tikuisis proves that once you get a PhD degree then you can be a professor with decent wages even though youre not good at it. His monotone is trying to hypnotise me every class and give as many examples as possible but only some of them will be on the exams. Class attendance is not really necessary, just spend your time on meaningful stuff.

Dudes, you are paying a lot of money for education, so you are not coming to classes because the prof is a nice person. This prof is really awkward and makes the classes extremely hard to follow due to his monotone. I won't show leniency to a prof because someone is nice, he needs to improve his lecture skills right now or nobody goes to classes.

I do not do math, like at all. Although he is very monotoned his explanations were very good and always did as many practice questions as the class needed. If I had to take a math class again I would love to have him teach it.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Greart guy, see a lot of people criticizing him for making it complicated. Based on what Ive seen online seems like its just a complicated course and if you go over the notes before class and watch a video or too for something you don't understand you will be more than fine. Midterms were very hard considering course material but not terrible.

He indeed doesnt know how to teach but he certainly is not the worst prof at uOttawa. People who gave him low ratings were either lazy or absent from classes. Just do the practice problems and the course is easy to get an A at least.

This can be the easiest math couse in math faculty, but his explanation makes the course ten times more confusing. You dont really have to go to classes each day, all you have to do is do the exercises and attend DGDs. Generally, he is not a bad person but his classes dont help much if you want to learn something useful.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Graded by few things', 'Test heavy']

rComments: With all classes moving online, we could finally understand how effective Prof Tikuisis's teaching method was. Because you have already taught yourself for half the semester. If you want to improve your self-learning skills to a maximum level, then Prof TIkuisis's class is the most suitable one. Thanks prof for preparing me for the online classes.

He tends to explain in such a way where hes explaining the material for himself, a math phd grad with 10 years of research, but not the class of second year undergrads. Even though the midterms were the same structure as practice midterms,the final was NOTHING like the practice final in terms of structures and difficulty after he said it would be

The prof was absolutely horrendous. The class itself wasnt hard at all, but he taught the class with ambiguity and boredom, which made you feel like that you were a piece of blank paper even after the lecture. Self-learning ability is a must-have thing for anyone taking his class.

His midterms are fair- just make sure to do the homework and ask questions before you get lost. It is also important to note that the final was very difficult. As someone who has an almost 10.0 GPA, the exam was brutal. There were proofs involved- something that was really unexpected as we had not done these in class. Go to his office hours please.

Horrible prof and the final was basically impossible. I did well on the midterms and studied a ton for the final and still had no idea how to solve most of the questions. Avoid his classes at all costs.

Very poor explanation skills, lectures are not engaging, and handwritting was a mess. His suggested exercises: the whole textbook (not helpful). Midterms were kinda fair, but final was disastrous with unrealistic expectations. Most wouldn't be surprised to have failed despite having a decent mark before. Also had multiple mistakes on each exam.
HORRIBLE final!
Professor Tikuisis made the final for this course exceptionally difficult and unrealistic considering the fair midterm.

With relatively fair midterms, the final was insanely hard, especially compared to the practice final he provided. Going into the final with a decent mark, but I might end up failing just because of the final.
Choose this professor if you want to FAIL the course.
Ridiculous Final exam
Final is impossible.
Terrible. The final exam was absurd compared to the midterms.
Hardest final Ive ever had. Avoid him.
Kind of boring, not great at answering questions, however the examples done in class are very useful and tests are often not very difficult.
Horrible. Don't chose his course.
So bad at explaining things.

Exams reflect very little from his lectures considering that his lectures are very difficult to follow. A very tough grader that doesnt really hand out part marks. He runs the DGD's as well so it's not like you are getting any other explanation. Also has extremely messy handwriting where + looks like t and u looks like v which in math is terrible.
A prof who doesn't explain things clearly.
Absolutely the WORST! Is BEYOND awful at explaining things!! and does not give enough examples. Exams feel like you don't know what ur doing
Highly recommended

He's a very awkward professor, he does not seem to know how to properly explain exactly the content of the class, all he does is read his slides and do some examples. His handwriting can be a little hard to read, but on the bright side, he posts all his notes and examples in class. My advice is to go to all your DGDs if you get him and practice.
Hes extremely bad at explaining the course material and his hand writing is hard to read so overall its very hard to follow along and it doesnt help that the course is already really hard.

Professor Tikuisiss lectures are boring and vague, and his PowerPoint files are not very helpful since it contains a lot of complex terms you dont know. He tries to do as many examples as he can to make students understand the procedure but it is hard to keep track. My advice is to go to DGD and check YouTube if you dont understand something.

His explanation is confusing and hard to understand, focus on explaining terminology that will not be tested instead of giving more examples of questions. Go to DGD, it is more helpful than the lectures.
Very helpful prof, a lot of the content can be confusing but he explains it pretty well and will give you extra help during office hours or by email if you ask

I was very worried going into my first Real Analysis course. However, I was pleasantly surprised. While the course was difficult and I had to work very hard, Tikuisis definitely made things as clear as possible and explained things very well. He also does his best to make classes engaging, and clearly has a sense of humour. Would take again.
confusing handwriting / courses move too fast
